  "prompt": "Why was Sundar Pichai chosen as the CEO of Google?",
  "response": "Sundar Pichai was chosen as the CEO of Google in 2015 and later became CEO of Alphabet (Google's parent company) in 2019 due to several key factors:\n\n1. Technical expertise: Pichai had a strong technical background and played crucial roles in developing successful Google products like Chrome, Chrome OS, and Google Drive.\n\n2. Leadership skills: He demonstrated exceptional leadership abilities and strategic thinking within the company, earning respect from employees and executives.\n\n3. Product vision: Pichai was instrumental in the development of several major Google products and showed a clear understanding of technology trends and user needs.\n\n4. Performance track record: He consistently delivered successful projects and helped grow Google's product portfolio.\n\n5. Cultural fit: He embodied Google's innovative and entrepreneurial culture and was well-aligned with the company's values.\n\n6. Internal recognition: He was trusted by Google's founders Larry Page and Sergey Brin, who saw him as a capable leader who could guide the company's future.\n\nWhen Larry Page restructured Google into Alphabet in 2015, he chose Pichai to lead Google, recognizing his potential to drive the company's growth and innovation. In 2019, he was further promoted to CEO of Alphabet, succeeding Page.\n\nHis background in engineering, combined with strong business and leadership skills, made him an ideal candidate for the role.",
